    <sect3 role="installation">
      <title>Installation of html5lib</title>

      <para>
        First, fix a build failure with Python 3.14 caused by the removal of
        several methods from the 'ast' module:
      </para>

<screen><userinput remap="pre">patch -Np1 -i ../html5lib-&html5lib-version;-python_3.14_buildfix-1.patch</userinput></screen>

      <para>
        <!-- Loosely based on upstream PR#592, primarily excluding additional
             guards that we don't need because we're only supporting
             setuptools-82 and later. -->
        Next, fix a build failure with setuptools-82.0.0:
      </para>

<screen><userinput remap="pre">sed -i 's/from pkg_resources import/from packaging.version import parse as/' setup.py &amp;&amp;
sed -i 's/import pkg_resources/pkg_resources = None/' setup.py</userinput></screen>

      <para>
        To build the <application>Python 3</application> module, run:
      </para>

&build-wheel;

      <para>
        To install the module, issue the following command as the &root; user:
      </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>&install-wheel; html5lib</userinput></screen>

      <para>
        This package does have a test suite, but it is not functional due to
        depending on several hardcoded versions of packages that are only
        usable with Python 3.6.
      </para>

    </sect3>

